      <h4><b>Cute Chia Pudding</b></h4>
      
      <div class="text-left">
<p class="title"><b>INGREDIENTS:</b></p>
<p class="title">1 Serving</p>
   <p>
      <li>2 Tbsp chia seeds</li>
      <li>1/2 Cup (125 ml) milk</li>
      <li>1/2 Tbsp honey</li>
      <li>4 Strawberies</li>
      <li>1 Kiwi</li>
      <li>5 Raw almonds</li>
  </p>
  </div>

  <div class="row">
    <div class="col-md-3"></div>
  <div class="text-left col-sm-12 col-md-6">
      <p class="title"><b>PREPARATION:</b></p>
      <li><b>1.</b> Combine chia seeds and milk in a bowl or jar and stir.</li>
      <li><b>2.</b> Keep the mixture in the fridge for at least 2 hours. (Overnight is recommended).</li>
      <li><b>3.</b> Stir and put half of it in a serving glass.</li>
      <li><b>4.</b> Crop 1 strawberry and 1 kiwi for decoration. Place them into the glass.</li>
      <li><b>5.</b> Add rest of mixture into the glass.</li>
      <li><b>6.</b> Put cropped almonds, strawberries and kiwies on the top.</li>
</div>
